<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Case Studies - How Creators Use BroqInsta</title>
    <meta name="robots" content="index, follow">
    <meta name="description" content="Discover how creators, marketers, and educators use BroqInsta to save and organize Instagram content for portfolios, analysis, and teaching.">
    <link rel="canonical" href="<%= siteUrl %>/case-studies">
    <meta property="og:type" content="website">
    <meta property="og:title" content="Case Studies - How Creators Use BroqInsta">
    <meta property="og:description" content="Discover how creators, marketers, and educators use BroqInsta to save and organize Instagram content for portfolios, analysis, and teaching.">
    <meta property="og:image" content="<%= siteUrl %>/images/preview.png">
    <meta property="og:url" content="<%= siteUrl %>/case-studies">
    <meta property="og:site_name" content="BroqInsta">
    <meta name="twitter:card" content="summary_large_image">
    <meta name="twitter:title" content="Case Studies - How Creators Use BroqInsta">
    <meta name="twitter:description" content="Discover how creators, marketers, and educators use BroqInsta to save and organize Instagram content for portfolios, analysis, and teaching.">
    <meta name="twitter:image" content="<%= siteUrl %>/images/preview.png">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/style.css">
    <script src="/js/tailwind.js"></script>
</head>

<body class="bg-[#FAFBFC] min-h-screen flex flex-col">
    <div class="hero-background">
        <div class="gradient-orb orb-1"></div>
        <div class="gradient-orb orb-2"></div>
        <div class="gradient-orb orb-3"></div>
    </div>

    <%- include('partials/header') %>

    <main class="flex-grow container mx-auto px-4 py-24 max-w-5xl">
        <nav class="mb-8 text-sm font-medium text-gray-400" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
            <ol class="flex items-center space-x-2" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/BreadcrumbList">
                <li itemprop="itemListElement" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/ListItem">
                    <a href="/" itemprop="item" class="hover:text-purple-600 transition-colors"><span itemprop="name">Home</span></a>
                    <meta itemprop="position" content="1">
                </li>
                <li><span class="mx-2">/</span></li>
                <li itemprop="itemListElement" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/ListItem">
                    <span itemprop="name" class="text-gray-600">Case Studies</span>
                    <meta itemprop="position" content="2">
                </li>
            </ol>
        </nav>

        <div class="text-center mb-20 stagger-in">
            <h1 class="text-64px font-black text-gray-900 mb-6">Case Studies</h1>
            <p class="text-xl text-gray-500 leading-relaxed font-medium italic max-w-2xl mx-auto">
                Real-world examples of how professionals leverage BroqInsta to streamline their Instagram content workflows.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="space-y-16">

            <div class="glass-card p-12 rounded-[2.5rem] animate-on-scroll">
                <div class="flex items-center mb-8">
                    <div class="w-16 h-16 bg-purple-100 rounded-2xl flex items-center justify-center text-3xl mr-6">🎨</div>
                    <div>
                        <h2 class="text-2xl font-black text-gray-900">Content Creator Portfolio</h2>
                        <span class="text-[10px] font-black uppercase tracking-widest text-purple-600">Creative Industry</span>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
                    <div>
                        <h3 class="text-xs font-black uppercase tracking-widest text-gray-400 mb-3">The Challenge</h3>
                        <p class="text-gray-500 leading-relaxed font-medium text-sm">
                            A freelance content creator with over 2,000 Instagram posts needed a reliable way to archive their best Reels and carousel posts for client pitches. Manually screenshotting and screen-recording content was time-consuming and resulted in low-quality files that failed to impress potential brand partners.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h3 class="text-xs font-black uppercase tracking-widest text-gray-400 mb-3">The Solution</h3>
                        <p class="text-gray-500 leading-relaxed font-medium text-sm">
                            Using BroqInsta, the creator downloaded their top-performing Reels and posts in original HD quality. They organized the files into themed folders — lifestyle, fashion, and travel — and embedded them directly into a professional portfolio website. The process that once took an entire weekend was completed in under two hours.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h3 class="text-xs font-black uppercase tracking-widest text-gray-400 mb-3">The Results</h3>
                        <div class="space-y-3">
                            <div class="flex items-center">
                                <span class="text-2xl font-black text-purple-600 mr-3">85%</span>
                                <span class="text-xs text-gray-400 font-bold">Faster portfolio assembly</span>
                            </div>
                            <div class="flex items-center">
                                <span class="text-2xl font-black text-purple-600 mr-3">3x</span>
                                <span class="text-xs text-gray-400 font-bold">More client inquiries per month</span>
                            </div>
                            <div class="flex items-center">
                                <span class="text-2xl font-black text-purple-600 mr-3">500+</span>
                                <span class="text-xs text-gray-400 font-bold">Posts archived in HD quality</span>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="glass-card p-12 rounded-[2.5rem] animate-on-scroll" style="transition-delay: 0.2s;">
                <div class="flex items-center mb-8">
                    <div class="w-16 h-16 bg-pink-100 rounded-2xl flex items-center justify-center text-3xl mr-6">📊</div>
                    <div>
                        <h2 class="text-2xl font-black text-gray-900">Marketing Team Workflow</h2>
                        <span class="text-[10px] font-black uppercase tracking-widest text-pink-600">Digital Marketing</span>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
                    <div>
                        <h3 class="text-xs font-black uppercase tracking-widest text-gray-400 mb-3">The Challenge</h3>
                        <p class="text-gray-500 leading-relaxed font-medium text-sm">
                            A 12-person marketing agency needed to track competitor Instagram strategies across 40+ brand accounts. Their analysts were spending roughly 15 hours per week manually cataloging competitor posts, stories, and Reels. The lack of a centralized archive made it difficult to identify content trends and report insights to clients.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h3 class="text-xs font-black uppercase tracking-widest text-gray-400 mb-3">The Solution</h3>
                        <p class="text-gray-500 leading-relaxed font-medium text-sm">
                            The team integrated BroqInsta into their weekly research workflow. Each analyst saved competitor Reels and high-performing posts directly to shared drives, organized by brand and campaign type. This created a living reference library that the entire team could access during strategy sessions and client presentations.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h3 class="text-xs font-black uppercase tracking-widest text-gray-400 mb-3">The Results</h3>
                        <div class="space-y-3">
                            <div class="flex items-center">
                                <span class="text-2xl font-black text-pink-600 mr-3">60%</span>
                                <span class="text-xs text-gray-400 font-bold">Reduction in research time</span>
                            </div>
                            <div class="flex items-center">
                                <span class="text-2xl font-black text-pink-600 mr-3">40+</span>
                                <span class="text-xs text-gray-400 font-bold">Competitor accounts tracked</span>
                            </div>
                            <div class="flex items-center">
                                <span class="text-2xl font-black text-pink-600 mr-3">2x</span>
                                <span class="text-xs text-gray-400 font-bold">Faster client report delivery</span>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="glass-card p-12 rounded-[2.5rem] animate-on-scroll" style="transition-delay: 0.4s;">
                <div class="flex items-center mb-8">
                    <div class="w-16 h-16 bg-blue-100 rounded-2xl flex items-center justify-center text-3xl mr-6">📚</div>
                    <div>
                        <h2 class="text-2xl font-black text-gray-900">Educator Resource Library</h2>
                        <span class="text-[10px] font-black uppercase tracking-widest text-blue-600">Education</span>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
                    <div>
                        <h3 class="text-xs font-black uppercase tracking-widest text-gray-400 mb-3">The Challenge</h3>
                        <p class="text-gray-500 leading-relaxed font-medium text-sm">
                            A high school media studies teacher curated educational Instagram content — infographics, short documentaries, and visual essays — to use as classroom examples. However, unreliable internet at the school and content being deleted by creators meant that lesson materials were frequently unavailable when needed most.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h3 class="text-xs font-black uppercase tracking-widest text-gray-400 mb-3">The Solution</h3>
                        <p class="text-gray-500 leading-relaxed font-medium text-sm">
                            The teacher used BroqInsta to download and permanently save educational Reels, carousel infographics, and video essays to a local drive. Each file was categorized by subject — digital literacy, visual storytelling, and social media ethics — ensuring offline access during every class session regardless of connectivity.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h3 class="text-xs font-black uppercase tracking-widest text-gray-400 mb-3">The Results</h3>
                        <div class="space-y-3">
                            <div class="flex items-center">
                                <span class="text-2xl font-black text-blue-600 mr-3">120+</span>
                                <span class="text-xs text-gray-400 font-bold">Educational resources archived</span>
                            </div>
                            <div class="flex items-center">
                                <span class="text-2xl font-black text-blue-600 mr-3">100%</span>
                                <span class="text-xs text-gray-400 font-bold">Offline lesson reliability</span>
                            </div>
                            <div class="flex items-center">
                                <span class="text-2xl font-black text-blue-600 mr-3">4.8/5</span>
                                <span class="text-xs text-gray-400 font-bold">Student engagement rating</span>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

        </div>

        <div class="mt-24 card-premium p-16 rounded-[4rem] text-center bg-white shadow-2xl animate-on-scroll">
            <h2 class="text-4xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-6">Ready to Build Your Own Success Story?</h2>
            <p class="text-gray-500 leading-relaxed font-medium max-w-2xl mx-auto mb-10">
                Join thousands of creators, marketers, and educators who trust BroqInsta for fast, reliable Instagram content downloads. Start saving your favorite content today.
            </p>
            <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-center justify-center gap-4">
                <a href="/" class="px-8 py-4 bg-gray-900 text-white rounded-2xl font-bold text-sm hover:bg-gray-800 transition-colors">
                    Start Downloading Now
                </a>
                <a href="/about" class="px-8 py-4 bg-purple-50 text-purple-700 rounded-2xl font-bold text-sm hover:bg-purple-100 transition-colors">
                    Learn About Us
                </a>
            </div>
            <div class="mt-8 flex items-center justify-center space-x-6 text-xs font-bold text-gray-400">
                <a href="/services" class="hover:text-purple-600 transition-colors">Our Services</a>
                <span>·</span>
                <a href="/about" class="hover:text-purple-600 transition-colors">About BroqInsta</a>
                <span>·</span>
                <a href="/blog" class="hover:text-purple-600 transition-colors">Read Our Blog</a>
            </div>
        </div>
    </main>

    <%- include('partials/footer') %>
</body>

</html>